Melania Trump, the First Lady of the United States, wrote a personal account of her experience with COVID-19. She revealed that she and her husband, President Donald Trump, tested positive for the virus two weeks ago. Melania expressed her initial concern for their son, who also tested positive but showed no symptoms. She shared that her symptoms included body aches, coughing, headaches, and extreme fatigue. Melania chose a natural approach to treatment, focusing on vitamins and healthy food. She expressed gratitude for the medical care she received and praised the healthcare workers and first responders. Reflecting on her illness, Melania emphasized the importance of living a healthy lifestyle and maintaining a positive mindset. She encouraged people to take care of their physical and mental well-being. Melania concluded by stating that she has tested negative and hopes to resume her duties soon. She expressed empathy for those who are sick or have loved ones affected by COVID-19 and offered prayers for their recovery.